00:13:02,257 --> 00:13:07,390
that the bulky spaceship, in a way,
personal spaceship,

245
00:13:07,390 --> 00:13:11,171
was not going to be very useful
for a practical application

246
00:13:11,171 --> 00:13:13,871
like servicing
the Hubble Space Telescope

247
00:13:13,871 --> 00:13:16,992
or assembly
of the International Space Station.

248
00:13:16,992 --> 00:13:18,902
So the project was abandoned,

249
00:13:18,902 --> 00:13:21,188
although it was
technically, really interesting;

250
00:13:21,188 --> 00:13:22,784
it had great capabilities,

251
00:13:22,784 --> 00:13:25,180
and operationally, it was
quite interesting also,

252
00:13:25,180 --> 00:13:26,889
but it was abandoned.

253
00:13:26,889 --> 00:13:28,422
What it was developed however

254
00:13:28,422 --> 00:13:31,752
is kind of a baby
of the Manned Maneuvering Unit,

255
00:13:31,752 --> 00:13:34,904
that it's called
Simplified Aid for EVA Rescue.

256
00:13:34,904 --> 00:13:36,976
The idea was the following:

257
00:13:36,976 --> 00:13:40,515
if you do a spacewalk
from the Space Shuttle,

258
00:13:41,145 --> 00:13:43,453
and normally you hold the structure,

259
00:13:44,463 --> 00:13:46,886
or you are on a portable foot restraint,

260
00:13:46,886 --> 00:13:48,845
or somehow, you are restrained,

261
00:13:48,845 --> 00:13:53,458
or you are possibly at the end
of the robotic arm on a holding platform,

262
00:13:54,958 --> 00:13:56,797
and then you have your safety tether;

263
00:13:56,797 --> 00:13:59,766
so, in case you don't hold
the structure anymore,

264
00:13:59,766 --> 00:14:03,686
you have the safety tether
to come back to the spaceship.

265
00:14:03,686 --> 00:14:05,438
Now, in the case of the Shuttle,

266
00:14:05,438 --> 00:14:07,448
in case you are not holding the structure,

267
00:14:07,448 --> 00:14:09,899
and your safety tether
was not attached properly,

268
00:14:09,899 --> 00:14:12,252
you would just drift away
from the Shuttle,

269
00:14:12,252 --> 00:14:14,768
but the Shuttle had
maneuvering capabilities

270
00:14:14,768 --> 00:14:16,755
and could come and rescue you.

271
00:14:16,755 --> 00:14:20,209
Normally, we were always two persons
doing the spacewalk,

272
00:14:20,209 --> 00:14:23,058
so one of them maybe
would be floating away,

273
00:14:23,058 --> 00:14:26,746
the Commander of the Shuttle,
or the pilot, would move the Shuttle,

274
00:14:26,746 --> 00:14:28,845
so that the other crew member,

275
00:14:28,845 --> 00:14:31,349
still attached with this safety tether
at the payload bay

276
00:14:31,349 --> 00:14:34,583
could grab his colleague
attached to the safety tether.

277
00:14:34,583 --> 00:14:40,562
And we had a third way of rescuing
the spacewalking crew member this way.

278
00:14:40,562 --> 00:14:42,350
Again, holding the structure is one way,

279
00:14:42,350 --> 00:14:44,366
safety tether is another way,

280
00:14:44,366 --> 00:14:46,611
the third way was motion
of the Space Shuttle

281
00:14:46,611 --> 00:14:49,332
towards the astronaut to be rescued.

282
00:14:50,252 --> 00:14:53,642
For the International Space Station
it is not possible,

283
00:14:53,642 --> 00:14:56,940
because the ISS can, of course,
control its orientation,

284
00:14:56,940 --> 00:14:59,346
its altitude, but it cannot translate.

285
00:14:59,346 --> 00:15:04,563
So if we had a spacewalking astronaut
in the vicinity of the Space Shuttle,

286
00:15:04,563 --> 00:15:06,428
suddenly detached from the structure,

287
00:15:06,428 --> 00:15:08,820
and the safety tether not safely attached,

288
00:15:08,820 --> 00:15:10,989
there would be no other way.

289
00:15:10,989 --> 00:15:15,182
In order to bring that third way,
rescuing the astronaut in this situation,

290
00:15:15,182 --> 00:15:19,521
NASA developed
the Simplified Aid for EVA Rescue.

291
00:15:19,521 --> 00:15:24,524
It's a mini Manned Maneuvering Unit,
but it would only allow

292
00:15:24,524 --> 00:15:28,053
the possibility for the crew member
to come back to the station

293
00:15:28,053 --> 00:15:30,663
after being detached inadvertently.

294
00:15:30,663 --> 00:15:33,673
And here you see,
it had to be attached

295
00:15:33,673 --> 00:15:36,239
